WEBVTT

00:05.538 --> 00:07.172
(THUNDER BOOMING)

00:07.273 --> 00:09.842
<i>♪</i>

00:21.955 --> 00:24.356
(SCREAMING)

00:24.358 --> 00:26.592
<i>♪</i>

00:35.168 --> 00:37.302
(BATS SCREECHING)

00:39.305 --> 00:42.241
(SNORING)
MAVIS: Pedro.

00:42.243 --> 00:43.409
Pedro!

00:43.411 --> 00:44.543
(KNOCKING)

00:44.545 --> 00:46.512
Pedro!
Wah!

00:46.514 --> 00:48.347
Aunt Lydia made me
dump out your mailbox

00:48.349 --> 00:50.783
since it's only been
piling up
for half a century.

00:50.785 --> 00:53.819
I have a mail box?
No way!

00:54.120 --> 00:54.853
Ooh.

00:54.855 --> 00:57.222
This one's from
my man Murray.

00:57.224 --> 01:01.827
"Dear Pedro,
don't embarrass me at
my boy Drac's hotel.

01:01.829 --> 01:04.296
"Oh, and I left
a refried screams burrito

01:04.298 --> 01:07.833
"under the bed a years ago.
You can have it."

01:07.835 --> 01:09.234
Sweet!

01:10.870 --> 01:12.137
(LAUGHS)

01:13.807 --> 01:16.642
Mmm. Free range maggots.

01:16.644 --> 01:18.977
Huh? Yay!

01:19.779 --> 01:23.248
The ancient scroll
of Four-Ply.

01:23.250 --> 01:24.983
I mean,
it's just toilet paper.

01:24.985 --> 01:28.520
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

01:28.522 --> 01:30.089
Grow hairy toenails!

01:30.091 --> 01:32.424
I just hauled
all your mail up.

01:32.426 --> 01:34.493
Grow 'em yourself. Ah!

01:34.495 --> 01:35.894
Ha!

01:36.062 --> 01:39.231
I am trying to curse you!

01:39.233 --> 01:41.600
This is my official invitation

01:41.602 --> 01:45.137
to compete in
the prestigious Curse Club!

01:45.139 --> 01:46.972
Tongue made of earwax!

01:46.974 --> 01:48.841
What's Curse Cl... Ugh!

01:48.843 --> 01:51.677
Aw! It's happening
all over again.

01:51.679 --> 01:53.812
What kind of
a mummy can't curse?

01:53.814 --> 01:55.881
I'll be thrown out
of every Mummy group!

01:55.883 --> 01:59.618
I remember when I tried
to lay my first curse.

02:00.720 --> 02:04.356
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION IN HIGH-PITCH)

02:04.358 --> 02:06.191
Grow hairy toenails!

02:07.527 --> 02:08.693
(ALL LAUGHING)

02:08.696 --> 02:10.662
PEDRO: <i>But it didn't work.</i>

02:10.663 --> 02:14.266
My mummy told me, one day,
I'd be invited to Curse Club,

02:14.268 --> 02:18.670
and on that day,
I'd finally be able
to lay a curse.

02:18.672 --> 02:20.405
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

02:20.407 --> 02:23.041
Witch warts for eyeballs!

02:23.043 --> 02:24.576
Um, I have to say
I'm pretty happy

02:24.578 --> 02:26.078
this isn't working out
for you.

02:26.080 --> 02:30.449
(SIGHING)
This is so humiliating.

02:32.385 --> 02:34.820
(LOUD MUNCHING SOUNDS)

02:34.822 --> 02:35.921
(BELCHING)

02:35.923 --> 02:38.490
I'm gonna go now.

02:39.259 --> 02:41.627
Pedro's been trying
his whole life

02:41.629 --> 02:43.562
and still can't
throw a curse.

02:43.564 --> 02:46.798
Dude's cursed,
except, y'know, not.

02:46.800 --> 02:48.467
You can't fake that stuff.

02:48.469 --> 02:51.003
(GASPING) Whoa!

02:51.005 --> 02:54.039
I just got
a genius idea!

02:54.041 --> 02:56.441
(SCOFFING) I hate to
be critical, Mavis,

02:56.443 --> 02:59.745
but do you ever feel like
it's your "genius ideas"

02:59.747 --> 03:00.546
that get you into trouble?

03:00.548 --> 03:07.019
Ooh, Wendy, you can't
make the same mistake
nine times. I hope.

03:07.021 --> 03:09.188
MAVIS: Hey, Pedro!
Looking good!

03:09.190 --> 03:10.689
I was telling
Hank and Wendy

03:10.691 --> 03:12.691
about the cool curses
you were throwing.

03:12.693 --> 03:16.361
Except I wasn't.
I'm a mummy that
can't curse!

03:16.363 --> 03:19.831
I might as well be a...
Whatever Wendy is.

03:19.833 --> 03:21.900
I'm a blob,
thank you very much.

03:21.902 --> 03:25.938
You know,
in some fish cultures,
we're considered royalty.

03:26.072 --> 03:28.307
Your Majesty.

03:29.209 --> 03:32.010
Come on, give it a try.
Do it! Do it! Do it!

03:32.012 --> 03:34.279
Please do it,
so she stops.
Do it! Do it! Do it!

03:34.281 --> 03:35.614
Do it! Do it! Do it!

03:35.616 --> 03:38.984
Seriously,
I'm very supportive
and even I hate it.

03:38.986 --> 03:40.352
(SIGHING) Fine.

03:40.354 --> 03:43.989
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

03:43.991 --> 03:46.225
Howl like a werewolf!

03:46.227 --> 03:48.193
(HOWLING)

03:48.494 --> 03:50.329
(GASPING)
(HOWLING)

03:50.331 --> 03:52.364
I did it!
She's howling!

03:52.366 --> 03:54.533
I cursed Mavis!
Yes, I did!

03:54.535 --> 03:58.303
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

03:58.305 --> 04:02.107
Hank and Wendy...
Swap bodies!

04:06.279 --> 04:07.512
(GASPING)

04:07.514 --> 04:08.614
I'm Hank!

04:08.616 --> 04:11.750
Ah, Look at me.
Ooh, I'm a blob.

04:11.752 --> 04:13.552
I have a name, you know.

04:13.554 --> 04:15.520
I did it again!

04:15.522 --> 04:18.790
Whoo-hoo! I can curse!

04:18.791 --> 04:19.725
Is he gone?

04:19.726 --> 04:22.661
Yup. Did you see
how happy he was?

04:22.663 --> 04:25.764
We did a good thing there,
pretending to be cursed.

04:25.766 --> 04:27.165
No, I didn't see anything.

04:27.167 --> 04:30.369
And all we did was give him
a false sense of confidence.

04:30.371 --> 04:34.172
Exactly. Now,
he can take some
pressure off his wraps.

04:34.174 --> 04:37.042
And all we have
to do is pretend
for a little while.

04:37.044 --> 04:38.644
What's the worst
that could happen?

04:38.646 --> 04:41.446
Don't you ever get
tired of saying that?

04:41.448 --> 04:42.881
Not really, no.

04:42.883 --> 04:45.050
MAVIS: Hope you
enjoyed your stay!

04:45.052 --> 04:48.153
(PEDRO LAUGHING)

04:48.155 --> 04:49.588
Uh...
(HOWLING)

04:49.590 --> 04:50.355
(BOTH GASPING)

04:50.357 --> 04:54.059
Sorry! Whatever I said,
I probably didn't mean it!

04:54.061 --> 04:55.427
Come again!

04:59.165 --> 05:02.934
(IN HIGH-PITCH)
Hi, Pedro!
Bleeeb, Blob, blob.

05:02.936 --> 05:04.836
I do not sound like that.

05:04.838 --> 05:05.404
Lookit, you guys.

05:05.406 --> 05:09.541
I've been waitin'
my whole life to throw
a curse and now,

05:09.543 --> 05:12.577
I'm doin' it
all over the place.

05:12.579 --> 05:13.912
Check this out!

05:13.914 --> 05:19.217
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

05:19.219 --> 05:21.920
You have two eyeballs!

05:21.922 --> 05:23.822
(GASPING)
PEDRO: It's not pretty,

05:23.824 --> 05:28.327
but still,
two eyeballs, baby!

05:28.861 --> 05:30.295
Aw, yeah!

05:30.297 --> 05:32.397
I'm so happy for you!

05:32.399 --> 05:35.133
I'm sure "Hank" is, too.

05:35.135 --> 05:38.070
Y'know if we knew
where he was.

05:38.072 --> 05:39.705
(SCATTING)

05:40.239 --> 05:43.909
Elevator up
to the penthouse, please?

05:44.077 --> 05:46.611
Oh my, we're going down!

05:46.613 --> 05:49.815
Ah, guess it looks
like this mummy

05:49.817 --> 05:53.518
is finally ready
for Curse Club!

05:53.520 --> 05:55.053
(GASPING)
Curse Club?

05:55.055 --> 05:57.422
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
What's the big deal?

05:57.424 --> 05:59.925
You couldn't have
asked that before?

05:59.927 --> 06:00.826
(GROWLING)

06:00.828 --> 06:04.329
<i>Welcome to another</i>
<i>exciting night of</i>
<i>Curse Club,</i>

06:04.331 --> 06:06.631
<i>where mummies lay curses</i>
<i>on each other</i>

06:06.633 --> 06:09.968
<i>until one walks away</i>
<i>a champion!</i>

06:09.970 --> 06:11.970
(GRUNTING)
<i>That's right, Skip.</i>

06:11.972 --> 06:13.405
<i>First rule of Curse Club is</i>

06:13.407 --> 06:15.607
<i>tell all your friends</i>
<i>about Curse Club!</i>

06:15.609 --> 06:18.043
<i>We're trying to get</i>
<i>the name out there.</i>

06:19.545 --> 06:20.812
Uh-oh.

06:20.814 --> 06:22.481
Now look
what you've done!

06:22.483 --> 06:24.983
You're about to see Pedro
go bandage-to-bandage

06:24.985 --> 06:28.120
in a battle of curses
against another mummy.

06:28.122 --> 06:29.354
A real one!

06:29.356 --> 06:30.956
(GULPING) Who?

06:31.691 --> 06:33.024
(GROWLS AND LAUGHS)

06:33.026 --> 06:37.562
Oh, she is gonna crush Pedro.
You've gotta do something.

06:37.564 --> 06:38.697
Why me?

06:38.699 --> 06:40.866
Oh, right.
Fake curses and all.

06:40.868 --> 06:42.267
(SPEAKING BLOBBISH)

06:42.269 --> 06:46.204
He says you're late for
your daddy-daughter lunch.

06:46.206 --> 06:47.873
But I'm not Wendy!

06:47.875 --> 06:51.643
Although, I do like
a free lunch.

06:52.412 --> 06:56.515
Wait a sec,
if we're all in
the Cerberus pit,

06:56.517 --> 06:58.216
where's the Cerberus?

06:59.285 --> 07:00.786
Uh-oh.

07:01.454 --> 07:03.889
Oh, you're a nice doggy,
aren't you?

07:03.891 --> 07:05.323
Yes, you're very soft.

07:05.325 --> 07:08.660
<i>So, we're just waiting</i>
<i>for a mummy dumb enough</i>

07:08.662 --> 07:12.898
<i>to get into the hexagon</i>
<i>with Queen Tutanhammer!</i>

07:14.600 --> 07:15.801
(GRUNTING)

07:15.803 --> 07:18.203
<i>Whaddya mean</i>
<i>there's someone there?</i>

07:18.205 --> 07:19.971
<i>Oh, it's Pedro!</i>

07:19.973 --> 07:23.909
<i>I couldn't see him</i>
<i>behind his behemoth</i>
<i>of an opponent.</i>

07:23.911 --> 07:25.177
<i>I guess he's dumb enough.</i>

07:25.179 --> 07:28.747
<i>I mean, why would anyone</i>
<i>want to battle her</i>
<i>on purpose?</i>

07:28.749 --> 07:31.650
(SCREAMING IN FRUSTRATION)
Okay, fine. I'll fix it.

07:31.652 --> 07:34.619
You don't have to be
so obvious about it!

07:36.088 --> 07:36.555
Mavis!

07:36.557 --> 07:39.424
Get outta here!
You're gonna get clobbered!

07:39.426 --> 07:40.659
No, you are.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.027
It's kinda, sorta,
very possible

07:42.029 --> 07:44.763
that you didn't actually
curse me or anyone.

07:44.765 --> 07:47.566
I faked it. I even drew
an eye on Mr. Donaldson.

07:47.568 --> 07:50.101
And it won't come off!
Sorry!

07:50.103 --> 07:52.237
Come on, you're just
saying all that

07:52.239 --> 07:54.172
to get me
out of the hexagon.

07:54.174 --> 07:56.241
Yes, because we faked it!

07:56.243 --> 07:58.844
You can't lay a curse
to save your life!

07:58.846 --> 07:59.478
Oh, yeah?

07:59.480 --> 08:00.912
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

08:00.914 --> 08:03.448
I curse you to be
a vampire forever!

08:03.850 --> 08:07.319
Boom, done,
run along now!
But, but, but...

08:12.625 --> 08:14.860
<i>And now for</i>
<i>the ceremonial offerings.</i>

08:14.862 --> 08:18.997
<i>Each mummy puts up what is</i>
<i>nearest and dearest to them.</i>

08:18.999 --> 08:20.165
See you real soon, Mom!

08:20.167 --> 08:23.435
I'm so proud of you,
baby girl!

08:23.870 --> 08:25.570
(SNAPS FINGERS)

08:25.872 --> 08:31.409
PEDRO:
My half-off burrito,
one-of-a-kind, VIP club card.

08:34.280 --> 08:34.980
(BELL RINGING)

08:34.982 --> 08:37.616
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

08:37.618 --> 08:39.683
Spider web! Ah!

08:40.219 --> 08:42.120
(LAUGHS)

08:42.421 --> 08:43.922
(GROANING)

08:44.222 --> 08:46.658
You're finished.

08:46.660 --> 08:47.692
He's right!

08:47.694 --> 08:51.129
Hmm... You're right.
I can do this!

08:51.131 --> 08:53.098
No one said that!

08:53.399 --> 08:56.735
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

08:59.906 --> 09:01.373
Turn to mush!

09:01.707 --> 09:03.141
(LAUGHING)

09:03.143 --> 09:04.309
Uh...

09:04.311 --> 09:05.076
(CRACKS KNUCKLES)

09:05.078 --> 09:07.679
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

09:09.015 --> 09:09.347
(GRUNTING)

09:09.349 --> 09:13.385
<i>Yes, Skip, of course</i>
<i>I'm sure Mavis know's</i>
<i>what she's doing.</i>

09:14.320 --> 09:15.020
(GROANS)

09:15.022 --> 09:19.024
<i>She always was</i>
<i>the "brains" of</i>
<i>the family!</i> (LAUGHS)

09:19.026 --> 09:20.692
(GRUNTING)

09:21.761 --> 09:24.563
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

09:25.364 --> 09:25.664
(EXCLAIMS)

09:25.666 --> 09:28.033
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

09:28.035 --> 09:31.937
<i>Looks like Queen Tut is gonna</i>
<i>send Mavis into Oblivion,</i>

09:31.939 --> 09:35.874
<i>which is actually quite nice</i>
<i>this time of year.</i>

09:35.876 --> 09:36.341
(GRUNTING)

09:36.343 --> 09:39.010
<i>Come on, I'm tryin' to</i>
<i>lighten the mood, Skip.</i>

09:39.012 --> 09:41.513
<i>My niece is gettin'</i>
<i>pummeled out there!</i>

09:41.515 --> 09:43.515
Mavis,
get outta there!

09:43.517 --> 09:44.282
(LAUGHING)

09:44.284 --> 09:47.152
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

09:47.154 --> 09:49.688
Grow hairy toenails!

09:50.723 --> 09:53.825
Did you just say
"grow hairy toenails?"

09:53.827 --> 09:56.728
Oh, no, she di'nt.
That one is mine!

09:56.730 --> 09:59.064
And no one curses
my friends!

09:59.198 --> 10:02.601
(SPEAKING UNINTELLIGIBLE
INCANTATION)

10:07.506 --> 10:09.240
Monkey Tail!

10:11.577 --> 10:14.813
Ah! Mouth sewn shut!

10:15.448 --> 10:16.414
(MUFFLED SPEAKING)

10:16.416 --> 10:19.484
<i>Yikes! Now he sounds</i>
<i>like you, Skipper.</i>

10:19.486 --> 10:22.087
<i>And if he can't speak,</i>
<i>it's over!</i>

10:22.089 --> 10:25.023
(BELL RINGING)
<i>Looks like</i>
<i>Queen Tutanhammer's</i>

10:25.025 --> 10:28.893
<i>gonna be bathing</i>
<i>in burritos tonight!</i>

10:29.328 --> 10:30.261
Ha!

10:30.263 --> 10:32.797
Half-off burritos!

10:32.799 --> 10:34.232
(MUFFLED SPEAKING)

10:34.234 --> 10:38.269
Pedro, I'm sorry
you lost your burritos.

10:38.471 --> 10:43.074
And I'm sorry
you had to go through all
those embarrassing curses.

10:43.076 --> 10:44.142
(LAUGHING) It's okay.

10:44.144 --> 10:47.312
I'm pretty sure the curses
have worn off already.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.347
(GASPING) Kapow!

10:49.349 --> 10:50.615
It worked! I can do it!

10:50.617 --> 10:54.352
I shouldn't have been shuttin'
my eyes all this time!

10:54.354 --> 10:55.387
What worked?

10:55.389 --> 10:57.989
Uh, nothing.
Never mind.

10:57.991 --> 11:01.493
Hey, what ever happened
to Hank and Wendy?

11:01.694 --> 11:07.065
Ahem. Uh, could you pass
the wartstershire sauce,
Daddy?

11:07.067 --> 11:08.900
(SPEAKING BLOBBISH)

11:08.902 --> 11:10.402
Thanks.

11:12.038 --> 11:15.206
(CRYING)
Oh, yes,
who's a good doggie?

11:15.208 --> 11:15.840
Yes, you are!

11:15.842 --> 11:20.145
Who's the softest doggie
in the world? Ooh, ooh!

11:20.613 --> 11:23.048
(BATS SCREECHING)

11:24.216 --> 11:29.554
LYDIA: Diane!
I cannot believe you're
abandoning me like this

11:29.556 --> 11:31.556
in my time of need!

11:31.558 --> 11:33.892
Talk about selfish!

11:33.894 --> 11:36.895
Everything okay,
Aunt Lydia?

11:36.897 --> 11:39.664
Ugh! Diane has
a chicken pock

11:39.666 --> 11:42.500
and she's being
so dramatic about it!

11:42.502 --> 11:44.903
<i>I bet she's not even sick.</i>

11:44.905 --> 11:47.639
(VIOLIN PLAYING)

11:49.909 --> 11:53.378
Ah, just as I'd suspected.

11:56.048 --> 11:57.482
Boo-berry!

11:57.484 --> 12:01.720
(COUGHING)
Chicken pock!

12:02.722 --> 12:03.321
MAVIS: Ooh!

12:03.323 --> 12:07.959
Look who ordered
a deluxe afternoon nap
from room service!

12:07.961 --> 12:14.065
This isn't a sleeping casket,
it's a rejuvenating casket.

12:14.067 --> 12:15.533
So, what's it do?

12:15.535 --> 12:16.267
If you must know,

12:16.269 --> 12:18.336
it keeps my bones
from turning to dust.

12:18.338 --> 12:21.239
A thousand years can really
take it's toll on a vampire.

12:21.241 --> 12:23.708
You'll see soon enough.
Oh, right.

12:23.710 --> 12:26.811
And since Diane has
flown the coop!

12:26.813 --> 12:30.982
Who's going to sit for an hour
and guard the casket now?

12:30.984 --> 12:31.716
Um, not to brag,

12:31.718 --> 12:34.686
but doing things for an hour
is kinda my thing.

12:34.688 --> 12:36.121
No one thinks that's a brag.

12:36.123 --> 12:38.590
I'm awesome at,
but not limited to,

12:38.592 --> 12:40.558
waiting for one hour
dry-cleaning,

12:40.560 --> 12:41.926
taking one hour lunch breaks,

12:41.928 --> 12:45.396
listing things I can do
in an hour in an hour.

12:45.398 --> 12:47.232
(SIGHING)
Very well.

12:47.234 --> 12:49.467
I shall put my faith
in this very specific

12:49.469 --> 12:54.672
and seemingly
insignificant skill
of yours.

12:54.674 --> 12:58.510
But, I am not to be disturbed
no matter the situation.

12:58.512 --> 13:01.212
And if I awake
with bones of dust,

13:01.214 --> 13:04.682
I will haunt
your soul forever!

13:05.251 --> 13:07.418
(GULPING)
Self-combusts.

13:07.420 --> 13:08.720
Gotcha.

13:09.922 --> 13:11.689
(TICKING)

13:11.691 --> 13:14.125
<i>♪ Stuck in this room</i>
<i>for one hour</i>

13:14.127 --> 13:16.561
<i>♪ Not gonna be bored</i>
<i>whatsoever!</i>

13:16.563 --> 13:19.998
<i>♪ One hour, one hour,</i>
<i>one hour, yeah! ♪</i>

13:20.000 --> 13:22.667
(JOINTS CRACKING)

13:25.504 --> 13:27.272
Ah-ha!
Just as I thought,

13:27.274 --> 13:30.975
this rug measures
three and a half me's.

13:37.783 --> 13:39.417
Boom drac-a-lacka!

13:39.419 --> 13:41.152
(CLEARING THROAT)

13:41.154 --> 13:43.087
"101 Ways to Count to Sixty."

13:43.089 --> 13:48.359
One-Transylvania,
two-Transylvania,
three-Transylvania...

13:48.361 --> 13:50.528
(SLURPING)

13:55.835 --> 13:57.168
Ah...

13:57.170 --> 13:57.802
Ah!

13:57.804 --> 14:00.071
That was only
two minutes? Ugh!

14:00.073 --> 14:01.439
And now, I gotta go
to the bathroom.

14:01.441 --> 14:04.175
How am I gonna do that
if I can't leave the room?

14:04.177 --> 14:06.344
Uh... Um...

14:06.879 --> 14:07.712
Nah, better not.

14:07.714 --> 14:11.349
Maybe I can hold it for...
57 and a half minutes?

14:11.351 --> 14:14.919
Guard this casket
with your life!

14:15.221 --> 14:18.857
(SHUDDERING) Okay,
I'll just be a minute.

14:18.859 --> 14:21.059
What could go wrong
in one minute?

14:21.061 --> 14:24.062
Stay. Stay, casket.

14:24.064 --> 14:25.797
Good casket.

14:28.000 --> 14:32.303
Everything the chicken
touched is contaminated.

14:32.305 --> 14:34.939
It's all gotta go!

14:34.941 --> 14:39.410
This, this, this.
Especially this.

14:39.412 --> 14:42.046
Uh, the painting's
contagious?

14:42.048 --> 14:46.584
No, but it'll really
brighten up
my waiting room.

14:48.020 --> 14:49.854
(GASPING)
What happened?

14:49.856 --> 14:51.322
(CAMERA CLICKS)

14:52.858 --> 14:53.858
Ah!

14:53.860 --> 14:56.361
Where is everything?

14:56.363 --> 14:58.529
Where's the casket?

14:58.531 --> 15:00.531
Check these out!

15:00.766 --> 15:03.301
MAVIS: What? No.

15:03.303 --> 15:04.702
(GASPING)

15:04.704 --> 15:06.437
The casket is out
with the trash?

15:06.439 --> 15:07.505
You could've led
with that!

15:07.507 --> 15:10.909
Yeah, but I look super cute
in the cooking one.

15:10.911 --> 15:12.377
True.

15:13.078 --> 15:15.446
<i>♪ We're gonna</i>
<i>drive, drive, drive</i>

15:15.448 --> 15:18.116
<i>♪ Until you sleep,</i>
<i>sleep, sleep! ♪</i>

15:18.118 --> 15:20.318
Wait a sec,
hold the mayo!

15:20.320 --> 15:22.387
(TIRES SCREECHING)

15:22.721 --> 15:24.956
(SCREAMING EXCITEDLY)
Do you know what this is?

15:24.958 --> 15:27.392
It's an antique bread box.

15:27.394 --> 15:31.296
Oh! I know your mother
said no more junk,

15:31.298 --> 15:33.331
but this isn't junk.

15:33.333 --> 15:35.333
(TIRES SCREECHING)

15:35.734 --> 15:37.936
Tell me Donald Cartright,
a known human,

15:37.938 --> 15:43.007
didn't just drive off
with Aunt Lydia,
a known human-hater.

15:43.009 --> 15:43.875
Donald Cartwright,
a known human,

15:43.877 --> 15:48.813
didn't just drive off
with Aunt Lydia,
a known human-hater.

15:48.815 --> 15:51.616
You're just saying that!
Because you told me to.

15:51.618 --> 15:54.352
I have 45 minutes
to get her back

15:54.354 --> 15:58.356
or I'm gonna self-combust!
(SCREAMING)

15:58.358 --> 16:03.227
(SCREAMING ECHOING)

16:03.229 --> 16:04.696
Ah! I should've
known Kitty

16:04.698 --> 16:06.264
would never let me
keep you in the house.

16:06.266 --> 16:10.068
I think she's jealous of
the jazzy wheels I added.

16:10.070 --> 16:12.337
She'd kill for a pair
of wheels like that!

16:12.339 --> 16:16.040
Hmm... What do you think
we should do with it?

16:16.042 --> 16:17.942
(COOING)

16:17.944 --> 16:20.678
You think
it'd be a nice ice box?

16:20.680 --> 16:22.380
(GIGGLING)
Okay!

16:22.382 --> 16:24.248
Give daddy
a hand, sweetie!

16:24.250 --> 16:25.650
(GIGGLING)

16:28.153 --> 16:30.989
Or a toolbox! Hmm?

16:31.457 --> 16:33.091
(BOTH LAUGHING)

16:33.093 --> 16:34.492
(COOING)

16:34.494 --> 16:34.726
Yes!

16:34.728 --> 16:38.262
We could cut it up
into teeny-tiny
flower planters!

16:38.264 --> 16:42.367
Mommy loves miniatures!
BRB with an axe!

16:42.369 --> 16:46.137
Don't go anywhere!
Ha-ha! As if.

16:46.505 --> 16:49.207
As if you would!
I'll be right back!

16:49.209 --> 16:51.709
Cut her in to
teeny tiny pieces?

16:51.711 --> 16:54.746
(GASPING)
This is serious. Look!

16:54.748 --> 16:56.280
He put wheels on it!

16:56.282 --> 16:56.981
(GASPING)

16:56.983 --> 16:59.450
Pedro, assume
the position!

16:59.452 --> 17:00.618
(LAUGHING)

17:00.620 --> 17:04.722
I put the "fly"
in "fishing."
(GRUNTS)

17:04.723 --> 17:06.491
Whee!

17:06.492 --> 17:08.393
(GRUNTS) Hook it.

17:08.395 --> 17:10.060
Nice cast!

17:10.729 --> 17:12.696
MAVIS: We got a live one!

17:12.699 --> 17:14.432
(ALL SCREAMING)

17:15.166 --> 17:18.069
Pedro, don't let go
of the casket!

17:18.070 --> 17:20.137
That's not a problem!

17:21.106 --> 17:22.673
(ALL STRAINING)

17:23.675 --> 17:27.878
Uh-oh. Pedro,
let go of the casket!

17:27.881 --> 17:30.148
(SCREAMING)

17:31.650 --> 17:32.950
(SCREAMING)

17:32.952 --> 17:37.889
Ha-ha! And that's how
Mumgee jumping is done!

17:38.290 --> 17:39.957
(GRUNTS AND LAUGHS)

17:39.959 --> 17:41.092
(PANTS) I can't look.

17:41.094 --> 17:43.327
Hey! Not looking
is my thing.

17:43.329 --> 17:47.432
Maybe the casket
fell into a roofless
pillow factory!

17:47.434 --> 17:48.232
We don't know.

17:48.234 --> 17:50.768
Nope. Not unless
pillow factories

17:50.770 --> 17:53.037
look like flimsy
tree branches.

17:53.039 --> 17:54.472
MAVIS: (GASPING)
It's safe!

17:54.474 --> 17:57.875
Okay, nobody move a muscle.

17:58.243 --> 17:59.577
Ah! Bee!

17:59.579 --> 18:01.446
(EXCLAIMING)

18:01.448 --> 18:02.980
Oh! Oh!

18:02.982 --> 18:04.849
(SCREAMING)

18:06.852 --> 18:09.720
(SCREAMING)

18:10.489 --> 18:11.389
Oh, I see the problem.

18:11.391 --> 18:14.158
What you shoulda said was,
"Nobody swat a bee,

18:14.160 --> 18:16.494
"dive over the cliff,
and land on the casket."

18:16.496 --> 18:17.829
MAVIS: Come on!

18:17.831 --> 18:19.097
(GRUNTS)

18:21.166 --> 18:23.234
I'm back!

18:23.368 --> 18:26.537
Box? Where are you,
buddy? Hello?

18:26.539 --> 18:29.740
<i>♪ Now here's a little ditty</i>
<i>'bout a casket on the loose</i>

18:29.742 --> 18:32.043
<i>♪ Speedin' like a train,</i>
<i>cargo in caboose</i>

18:32.045 --> 18:34.245
<i>♪ 28 minutes said the number</i>
<i>on the clock</i>

18:34.247 --> 18:36.714
<i>♪ Till Mavis goes bye-bye,</i>
<i>tick-tock-tick-tock</i>

18:36.716 --> 18:39.717
<i>♪ Babysit a casket was</i>
<i>all she had'ta do, jeez ♪</i>

18:39.719 --> 18:42.353
<i>♪ Hey, what's chasing you</i>
<i>kids, is that... ♪</i>

18:42.355 --> 18:45.423
Bees! Why is it always bees?

18:45.425 --> 18:47.425
(SCREAMING)
(ROARING)

18:50.162 --> 18:52.063
(CHITTERING)

18:52.065 --> 18:54.198
Come on,
pillow factory!

18:54.200 --> 18:57.668
<i>♪ Didn't see that coming,</i>
<i>what an unexpected twist</i>

18:57.670 --> 19:02.073
<i>♪ Is it curtains for the kids?</i>
<i>Will they cease to exist? ♪</i>

19:02.075 --> 19:04.108
(ALL SCREAMING)

19:13.519 --> 19:15.786
(STUTTERS) Can we take
the long way home?

19:15.788 --> 19:16.420
(GASPING)

19:16.422 --> 19:20.558
Uh, yeah, sure!
We've got loads of time.

19:20.560 --> 19:23.060
We can totally
take the long way.

19:23.062 --> 19:24.962
Yes!
(BOTH GRUNTING)

19:24.964 --> 19:26.998
(HANK SCREAMING)

19:27.000 --> 19:29.600
One minute! (GASPING)

19:29.902 --> 19:32.103
(ALL SCREAMING)

19:32.671 --> 19:33.905
PEDRO: Ha-ha!

19:33.907 --> 19:35.206
Nobody look!

19:36.608 --> 19:37.775
(CLUCKING)

19:37.777 --> 19:39.177
(CLUCKING)

19:39.179 --> 19:40.478
A flying casket?

19:40.480 --> 19:42.914
Your fever must
be getting worse.

19:42.916 --> 19:44.382
More ice!

19:45.284 --> 19:46.217
(CLUCKING)

19:46.219 --> 19:49.320
Hank, I need
to see to steer!

19:49.322 --> 19:53.324
Ah! Flip-flop
casket roll! Now!

19:53.326 --> 19:54.258
(ALL STRAINING)

19:54.260 --> 19:57.361
Ha-ha!
How low can we go?

19:57.363 --> 19:59.230
Just low enough!

19:59.232 --> 20:00.765
HANK: Uh... Slow down!

20:00.767 --> 20:02.533
This thing doesn't
come with brakes.

20:02.535 --> 20:03.568
(HANK SCREAMING)

20:03.570 --> 20:06.737
I got this!
(ALL GRUNTING)

20:09.741 --> 20:11.042
Whee!

20:11.044 --> 20:13.978
(LAUGHING)
Look at that!

20:13.980 --> 20:15.079
Whee!

20:15.081 --> 20:17.315
(GASPS)
And just in time!

20:17.317 --> 20:19.250
(ALL STRAINING)

20:19.484 --> 20:21.886
ALL: Three, two, one.

20:21.888 --> 20:23.287
(BELL DINGING)

20:26.959 --> 20:28.259
(SIGHS IN RELIEF)

20:28.261 --> 20:30.127
I feel great!

20:30.129 --> 20:32.230
But you look
terrible, child.

20:32.232 --> 20:35.566
How taxing can it be
to just watch something?

20:35.568 --> 20:37.301
You have no idea.

20:37.303 --> 20:40.004
What did I tell ya, huh?
Safe and sound.

20:40.006 --> 20:42.673
Mavis the casket-watcher
to the rescue.

20:42.675 --> 20:45.576
I suppose
I underestimated
your ability

20:45.578 --> 20:49.213
to sit and stare
at something.

20:49.881 --> 20:52.683
What happened to my room?

20:52.685 --> 20:56.587
Um, ah, well, ah, all you
said was guard the casket

20:56.589 --> 20:58.322
with your life and, ah,
believe me, we did.

20:58.324 --> 21:01.626
(STAMMERING)
Everything Diane touched
had to be thrown out...

21:01.628 --> 21:06.430
moved out to my office
for... Observation.

21:07.332 --> 21:10.935
Ah, well, at least
that spiteful chicken

21:10.937 --> 21:13.971
didn't get her claws
on my casket.

21:18.076 --> 21:19.510
Toss the casket.

21:19.512 --> 21:20.845
And the bird!

21:20.847 --> 21:22.179
(CLUCKS)

21:23.081 --> 21:26.450
(STRAINING) Phew!

21:26.452 --> 21:29.353
Who knew watching
a rejuvenation casket

21:29.355 --> 21:32.757
for an hour could
make you so tired?

21:34.192 --> 21:36.360
(CLUCKING)

21:40.999 --> 21:43.501
Gah! There she is!

21:49.641 --> 21:51.742
(BRAKES SQUEALING)

21:53.512 --> 21:56.814
(SCREAMING HAPPILY)
I can't believe it!

21:56.816 --> 21:57.181
(LAUGHING)

21:57.183 --> 22:01.686
I knew you'd find
your way back to me.
I just knew it!

22:02.554 --> 22:05.122
Thank you,
pillow factory!

22:06.391 --> 22:09.093
<i>♪</i>
